        "question": "Should I build microservices from the start or start with a monolith?",
        "answer": "For most new products: start with a well-structured monolith. Microservices add significant operational overhead — service discovery, distributed tracing, inter-service authentication, distributed transactions. This overhead is worthwhile when you have multiple teams who need to deploy independently, or when you need independent scaling for different parts of your system. Build the monolith with clean internal boundaries and clear domain separation — this makes eventual decomposition much easier if and when it's needed."
