        "question": "How does UK GDPR interact with microservices?",
        "answer": "Microservices create interesting GDPR challenges. Personal data may flow through multiple services — each acting as a data processor for the data controller (your platform). Key considerations: (1) Right to erasure — you must be able to find and delete personal data across all services that have processed it; (2) Audit logging — log which service processed which personal data, when, for which purpose; (3) Data minimisation — only pass personal data between services that genuinely need it; (4) Event sourcing GDPR tension — immutable event logs conflict with right to erasure; use cryptographic erasure (delete the encryption key for a user's events)."
